ANC Secretary General Ace Magashule has apparently suspended party President Cyril Rampaphosa. That's after Magashule himself was suspended. ANC Spokesperson, Pule Mabe clarifies. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC spokesperson Pule Mabe, says the Secretary-General does not have the authority to make unilateral decisions. That's after reports that Ace Magashule has issued a suspension letter to party President Cyril Ramaphosa. READ: Magashule 'suspends' Ramaphosa The ANC says it has seen the letter but won't discuss its contents. Mabe says any decision regarding a suspension should come from the National Executive Committee not an individual.